org.jamsim.io

Class FileLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamsim.io.FileLoader

  • public class FileLoader
extends java.lang.Object
    File loader that loads datasets, and objects based on datasets, from files. The location of files is determined by the preferences or a GUI prompt.
    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion

      • getFile

        public java.io.File getFile(java.lang.String prefsKey)
                     throws java.io.IOException

        Parameters:
        prefsKey - key to lookup stored filename.
        Returns:
        File specified in prefs, or selected in the dialog by user.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if no valid file is selected when prompted.

                   javax.swing.filechooser.FileFilter filter,

        prompt - prompt message to ask user to select a file.

      • loadJSONMarkedUpBeans

        public <E extends CMarkedUpRowBean> java.util.Collection<E> loadJSONMarkedUpBeans(java.lang.String prefsKey,
                                                                         java.io.File file,
                                                                         java.lang.Class<E> beanClass)
                                                                       throws java.io.IOException
        Load CDataFileDef from prefs key, then load file using the CDataFileDef. Returns a collection of CMarkedUpRowBeans. CMarkedUpRowBean#setMarkedUpRow(net.casper.data.model.CMarkedUpRow) is called on every bean.
        Type Parameters:
        E - type of bean class
        Parameters:
        prefsKey - preferences key specifying location of CDataFileDef.
        file - file containing data specified by the CDataFileDef.
        beanClass - CMarkedUpRowBean class to load
        Returns:
        collection of CMarkedUpRowBeans.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if problem reading file or creating beans

      • loadDataset

        public CDataCacheContainer loadDataset(CDataFile cdef)
                                throws java.io.IOException
        Supplies a File to a CDataFile and loads the dataset. The file to load is specified by looking up the file location in the preferences. If the file is not set in the preferences, or does not exist, a dialog box is shown allowing the user to select the file location. During loading progress is displayed via this instance's output object (supplied to the constructor).
        Parameters:
        cdef - CDataFile object describing the dataset to load.
        Returns:
        a casper container
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem loading the file.

      • loadUnspecifiedDataset

        public CDataCacheContainer loadUnspecifiedDataset(java.lang.String datasetName)
                                           throws java.io.IOException
        Loads a dataset with no columns or primary key specified. The loaded dataset is narrowed. The file to load is specified by looking up the file location in the preferences. If the file is not set in the preferences, or does not exist, a dialog box is shown allowing the user to select the file location. During loading progress is displayed via this instance's output object (supplied to the constructor).
        Parameters:
        datasetName - name describing the dataset to load. Used to lookup the file location in preferences.
        Returns:
        a casper container
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem loading the file.
